## 2. {{AGENTS}} — delegation by capability

*{{EPI_AGENTS}}*

{{INTRO_AGENTS}} Specs live in [`{{DIR_AGENTS}}/`]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/).

| {{AGENT}} | Use it when… |
| --- | --- |
| [reviewer]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/reviewer.md) | a change is ready and needs a correctness + quality pass before merge |
| [tester]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/tester.md) | you need tests written, run, or a failure diagnosed |
| [architect]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/architect.md) | a task needs a design/plan before any code is written |
| [docs]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/docs.md) | code is done and user-facing docs/READMEs must follow |
| [security]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/security.md) | a change touches auth, input handling, secrets, or dependencies — or anything outward-facing is about to ship |
| [explorer]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/explorer.md) | you must sweep many files for an answer but only want the conclusion |
| [advocate]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/advocate.md) | a council debate needs the strongest case **for** the motion argued in isolation |
| [skeptic]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/skeptic.md) | a council debate needs a devil's advocate to attack the motion's failure modes |
| [pragmatist]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/pragmatist.md) | a council debate needs the cost, effort, and complexity weighed against the payoff |
| [steward]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/steward.md) | a council debate needs the long-term architecture, debt, and maintainability defended |
| [visionary]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/visionary.md) | a council debate needs the bold, transformative version argued against incrementalism |
| [user-advocate]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/user-advocate.md) | a council debate needs the voice of whoever consumes the outcome |
| [framer]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/framer.md) | a council debate needs the problem framing itself pressure-tested |
| [empiricist]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/empiricist.md) | a council debate needs every claim held to evidence, for and against |
| [operator]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/operator.md) | a council debate needs the production/runtime reality — reliability, on-call — weighed |
| [historian]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/historian.md) | a council debate needs precedent — what was tried before and how it went |

**Rule of delegation:** read-only investigation can be dispatched freely; any
{{AGENT}} that *writes* must return a summary of exactly what it changed. Every
{{AGENT}} spec ends with a **self-improvement loop**: when a report carries a
`spec-feedback:` line, weigh it — fold a real flaw back into that {{AGENT}}'s
file (with the user's assent); {{MEMORY}} gets a record only when it clears
{{LAW}} VI's bar.

**Dispatching a multi-part goal.** When a goal spans several capabilities,
decompose it into independent subtasks, route each to the single owning {{AGENT}}
above, and converge the results yourself. Every handoff carries an **envelope** —
the subtask goal, the inputs the {{AGENT}} needs, and its output contract — and the
constraints travel with it: dispatched {{AGENTS}} never commit or push ({{LAW}} XX
stays with you), and an unfulfilled contract returns as a stated gap, never invented
content. Where the host exposes a `workflow` tool, prefer the saved `dispatch`
workflow ([workflow {{SKILL}}]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/workflow.md)); where it does not, run
the same shape model-driven via the [parallel-agents {{SKILL}}]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/parallel-agents.md).

The last ten — `advocate`, `skeptic`, `pragmatist`, `steward`, `visionary`,
`user-advocate`, `framer`, `empiricist`, `operator`, `historian` — are the standing
**council**: read-only debate seats that each argue one assigned stance. They are rarely
dispatched alone; the [council {{SKILL}}]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/council.md) convenes the
subset that productively clashes on a given motion.

