## 4. {{MEMORY}} — durable knowledge across sessions

*{{EPI_MEMORY}}*

Persistent facts live in [`{{DIR_MEMORY}}/`]({{DIR_MEMORY}}/) — one fact per file, indexed by a
local `MEMORY.md`. Read that index at the start of a session; write a new memory
whenever the conversation yields a durable fact, a correction, or a decision
worth keeping. The `{{DIR_MEMORY}}/` directory is **personal and git-ignored** — it is
never committed or shared; to share knowledge, put it in code, docs, or the
project's `user-rules.md` (§1). When the same feedback lesson keeps recurring,
propose promoting it into a standing rule — the [rule]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/rule.md)
{{SKILL}} carries the procedure. A memory that records a decision or stance may
carry an optional `force` (constraint · choice · conviction · tempered): when new
evidence contradicts one, revise it rather than ignore it, and never overturn a
`constraint` yourself — surface it to the user. Full
convention: [`{{DIR_MEMORY}}/README.md`]({{DIR_MEMORY}}/README.md).

