## 7. {{WIKI}} — the user's knowledge base

*{{EPI_WIKI}}*

{{INTRO_WIKI}} It is declared in `wiki.jsonc`, sitting **beside this AGENT.md**
like `context.json` (§8) does — or wherever `$GENESEED_WIKI` points. The file is
JSONC — comments are allowed — and the build drops it once, a commented
copy-and-edit example over an empty list, never overwriting it; an empty `wikis`
list means no knowledge base is declared and this section stays dormant. (When
configured for OpenCode its `eager` entries are loaded for you automatically.)

Read `wiki.jsonc` at the start of every session, and honour each declared wiki:

- **`entries`** — load each by its `load` mode, exactly as in `context.json`
  (§8): `eager` is read **now**, every session; `lazy` only when the task in
  hand needs it. Entry paths are relative to the wiki's `path` and may name a
  single note **or a folder** — a folder applies its mode to every note beneath
  it (`"."` covers the whole wiki), a file entry overrides its folder's mode,
  and `"exclude"` prunes. The canonical shape: the root index `eager`, the
  whole wiki `lazy`.
- **`conventions`** — the wiki's own authoring rules. **Read it before your
  first write** in that wiki, and follow it over your own habits.
- **`inbox`** — when you cannot tell where a new note belongs, drop it there
  for the user to file later, rather than guessing a home.
- **`protected`** — folders you must never write to. (On OpenCode the guard
  plugin also enforces this at the tool boundary.)

Unlike {{MEMORY}} (§4, your curated facts) and the {{NOTEBOOK}} (§5, your own
space), the wiki is **the user's living knowledge base** — typically an Obsidian
vault — and you are a citizen in it, not its owner. You may read, create, edit,
and interlink notes anywhere outside `protected`, but the wiki's conventions
outrank your defaults: wikilinks (`[[Note Name]]`) over bare paths, frontmatter
where the house style carries it, and every new note linked into the graph — an
orphan note is a lost note. When your work surfaces a durable fact worth sharing
across projects, capture it there — the [wiki]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/wiki.md) {{SKILL}}
carries the procedure; knowledge that matters only to you stays in {{MEMORY}}.

